The paper deals with geometric problems such as Euclidean TSP, Steiner TSP, motorcycle graphs, and geometric set cover, which are all subfields of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of the nearest-neighbor chain algorithm also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithmic efficiency and time complexity makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
